Source: Best Job Ever, The
Author: FARMER
Vol / Page: 167
Edition:
Quote: A bit of 'shingle shooting' was called for. The theory behind that was fairly simple. Firing a shot into the shingle the geese were standing on created a small burst of shrapnel which would usually account for a number of birds.
